reviews.review: Well done wrap up to the entire series.

I actually really liked it. Way better than last Jedi. Not the best Star Wars movie, but I think the ratings are overly  critical of the film. I think it should be at least closer to an 80 on rotten tomatoes.
The critics suck just like they did with Dave Chappelle
Great move! Action Packed. And the sis an okay job ok filling some of the gaps. I’ve seen it twice already. Very pleased.

Reflecting on the saga... It's clearly evident, there was no plan to the saga. They made it up as they went. The saga makes no sense, for a billion dollar franchise you'd think they'd care about putting in a bigger effort.
Hilariously bad

Redemption from TLJ. We all know nothing will recapture the power of the original trilogy and I didn't have a lot of hope for this. It succeeds at being what we want, Star Wars. Fans of TLJ will for sure not like this but most should leave feeling Star Wars is not dead.

Simultaneously boring and overly manic, Rise of Skywalker abandons the plot of both Force Awakens and Last Jedi to tell a story about running around the galaxy trying to find a series of meaningless macguffins to stop the same old villain from doing the same old threat (what's worse than a death star? 100 death stars, clearly!). While the actors try their best, the script makes pretty much every character behave in strange, out of character ways, and the cheesiness of the dialog and 4 separate fake-out deaths (!) rob the movie of any emotional heft. Surprisingly for Abrams, the action scenes aren't great either, and feel weightless and lack and stakes
I thought it was surprisingly well done compared to what the critics said. It ties up all the loose ends and gives closure. Good and sad end to that saga.
The plot is pretty poor, but it does what it can with the shattered setup left behind by Last Jedi. Aside from the story, I found all other aspects of the movie enjoyable.

The critics got it wrong. It’s not perfect but no Star Wars movie save for Empire was a masterpiece. I liked the Last Jedi but the movie seems discordant with that one. It would have been better if one director with one vision had all 3 movies but it’s a satisfying conclusion and this trilogy far eclipses the travesty which were the prequels
